Red Bull's Dutch driver Max Verstappen drives during the first day of the Formula One (F1) pre-season testing at the Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya in Montmelo. AFP/Lluis Gene BARCELONA - Red Bull's new car ahead of the new season has finally been revealed to the public. Reigning world champion Max Verstappen showed the RB18 design for the first time during practice in Barcelona. The RB18 had already completed a private shakedown at Silverstone before the first test, but no images were released. Verstappen is sporting the number 1 on his car for his title defence after beating Lewis Hamilton to last year's championship. The Dutch driver clinched the title in the dramatic  Abu Dhabi Grand Prix final race.